snippet.textDisplay:
I can’t stand mother effers who have the audacity to say that she kept her pregnancy a SECRET. No bitches she kept it PRIVATE!!! Learn the difference. The word HIDING has such a negative connotation behind it and it’s disrespectful to use it when it comes to a woman’s decision of putting boundaries to her personal life. Hella people came after me for “HIDING” my pregnancy, my baby and my husband and it was so fricken annoying because we truly live in a world where if it’s not posted on social media, it’s not validated. & I’m not even a social media influencer!! I kept my pregnancy PRIVATE as fuck and i had the most beautiful healthy pregnancy and delivery. The easiest first pregnancy ever. It was the most amazing time of my life. I didn’t post a damn thing about my pregnancy or my delivery or my baby until she was 3 months old and it was the best decision I made in regards to my family and myself. I recently posted about my pregnancy a few weeks ago after my daughter turned 3 months old and chile... when I tell you the audacity people have. Privacy is sometimes always the best route to go when it comes to personal life situations. Especially in this day and age. Prayers to you Elsy. Never be ashamed to be who you are and what route you choose in your life. Your life is yours to live.
P.S sorry for cussing I’m just hella passionate about trolls trying to tear down a pregnant woman.
